messages.message: @Xindi Xu on localhost I'm getting `Your organization's license has expired. Contact Instabase Sales to set up a license.` all of a sudden. Is there a way I can fix this? I still can't see my org in aihub-sandbox as an admin :confused:
@Victor Zeng could you help out here?
btw, your local host is probably using dogfood DB, not aihub-sandbox DB

and if so, how do i change that?
not sure where our DB creds are for aihub-sandbox
no, we can't use aihub-sandbox DB
are you saying that i should use local db then?
you can use either local or dogfood DB

> btw, your local host is probably using dogfood DB, not aihub-sandbox DB
Yup I know that. I guess im just trying to understand why you said this
I think she said it b/c that explains why you can't see your org in aihub-sandbox as an admin
@Dominic Fannjiang let me know what environment (laptop, aihub-sandbox, aihub-uat, etc.) and your username and I'll look to find out why the license expired for the org you belong to.

ahh got it, makes sense. So yes, im connected to dogfood DB, but developing locally. the account im using that is a commercial user is `<mailto:dominic.fannjiang+test_org_setup@instabase.com|dominic.fannjiang+test_org_setup@instabase.com>`
